[[File:ShaperHand-FF40.png|thumb|right|250px|Shaper Adept [[Nen Yim]]'s shaper hand]]
'''Shaper hands''' were cephalopoidal creatures used by the [[shaper caste]] of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]. When a [[Shaper Adept]] was [[Escalation|escalated]] to the rank of [[Master Shaper]], they sacrificed one&mdash;or both&mdash;of their hands and attached the creatures to where their hands had been. The fingers of shaper hands were implanted with the tools necessary in [[Shaping protocol|shaping]]. Often, shapers would place weapons in the tentacles of the hand, such as [[finger-spear]]s.

[[Initiate (Shaper)|Shaper Initiates]] had a similar organism to replace their right hands on their escalation to Adept, but these creatures had five digits instead of eight.

